text: Silberbach may refer to: *Silberbach (Heubach), a river of North Rhine- Westphalia, Germany, tributary of the Heubach *Silberbach (Franconian Rezat), a river of Bavaria, Germany, tributary of the Franconian Rezat *Silberbach, a river of Bavaria, Germany, a bifurcation of the Kaltenmühlbach *Silberbach, a river of Carinthia, Austria, that flows through Guttaring *Cisnădie (river), German name Silberbach, a tributary of the river Cibin in Romania *Silberbach, a village in Upper Franconia, Bavaria, Germany, today part of the municipality Konradsreuth *Stříbrná, German name Silberbach, a village and municipality in the Karlovy Vary Region of the Czech Republic *Strużyna, Warmian-Masurian Voivodeship, German name Silberbach, a village within Ostróda County, Warmian- Masurian Voivodeship, Poland
title: Silberbach
